---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — AstroStatic" description="Learn about AstroStatic, a content-first static site starter built with Astro 5 and Tailwind CSS.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">About AstroStatic</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
        AstroStatic is a production-ready starter for building content-heavy static websites with
        <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Astro 5</a>,
        <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">Tailwind CSS 4</a>,
        and TypeScript.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">What we built</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            <li>Zero JavaScript by default — pure static HTML output</li>
            <li>Blog with content collections and Zod schema validation</li>
            <li>RSS feed at <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">/rss.xml</code></li>
            <li>Sitemap generation via <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">@astrojs/sitemap</code></li>
            <li>Dark mode with system preference detection</li>
            <li>Accessible navigation with skip-to-content link</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Tech stack</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Astro 5</strong> — island architecture, content collections</li>
            <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Tailwind CSS 4</strong> — via <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">@tailwindcss/vite</code> plugin</li>
            <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">TypeScript</strong> — strict mode enabled</li>
            <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">@astrojs/rss</strong> — feed generation</li>
            <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">@astrojs/sitemap</strong> — SEO sitemap</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Getting started</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
        Clone the repository, install dependencies, and start the dev server:
      </p>
      <pre class="rounded-lg bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-4 text-sm overflow-x-auto mb-8"><code>npm install
npm run dev</code></pre>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        Add blog posts as Markdown files in <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">src/content/blog/</code> and
        new pages as <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">.astro</code> files in <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">src/pages/</code>.
        See the <a href="/blog" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">blog</a> for examples.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
